Commentary Text: Narine to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Shivam Mavi!! Outstanding by Cummins. A pity that the catch will not have his name. Tossed up full from round the wicket on off, Riyan Parag lofts powerfully and Cummins on the long-off fence runs and takes it overhead to his right, but his balance and momentum are taking him towards the cushions, so he flicks the ball to Mavi who is coming in from long-on. Mavi has to leap a little and sticks his right hand out to hang on. The umpires check for a clean catch and it is one. Terrific athletic ability from Cummins made that catch possible. Riyan Parag c Shivam Mavi b Narine 5(3) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Narine to Padikkal, out Bowled!! Respite for KKR. Padikkal does not know what happened there. He looks surprised that he has missed it. Slower on off, shorter as well, but the knuckle-ball pushed from the front of the hand, Padikkal was early into the pull, way too early and misses, the ball flicks the off-bail off. Commentary Text: Boult to Shreyas Iyer, 1 run, almost another run out! Had Boult picked this up cleanly, he would have had a clear shot at the non -striker's stumps and Iyer would have been well short. As it turns out, the NZ pacer can't gather it properly. Relief for Finch, the last thing he needs right now is to run his skipper out. In-angler, tucked towards the short mid-wicket region and there was a lot of hesitation before the batters went for the run. Fortunately for KKR, it doesn't cost them

Commentary Text: Boult to Finch, out Narine Run Out!! A suicidal run out to start the innings! Atrocious call from Finch, timed this push-drive so well towards cover and kept running with the shot. Narine had to respond, but this was always a risky single. And it's made to look even more silly with Hetmyer's fiery direct hit at the striker's end. Narine is yards out. What a waste of a wicket this is! The West Indian was clearly promoted to maximise the powerplay but now has to depart without facing a single delivery. Quite sure that Finch will be feeling immense guilt at the moment. Narine run out (Hetmyer) 0(0)
